Where get_component implicitly operates on the current snapshot — since in the single user case there's rarely a reason to query a historical snapshot directly.
Or go further and ask whether Snapshot needs to exist at the interface level at all, and just let it be an internal implementation detail of the SQLite backend — the thing that makes the append-only log work. The interface then becomes:
pythonclass SpecStore(Protocol):
    def store_snapshot(self, components: list[Component]) -> None: ...
    def list_components(self) -> list[Component]: ...
